    "This helps conserve water.",
    "Being a novel sector, production and sale of insects as feed faces several challenges, from legal to consumer acceptance and to industrialization and growth.",
    "Although the legal framework is changing and adapting to this new reality, consumers still have to prepare for it, and insect producers have a lot to learn from other livestock and industrial sectors (Alhujaili et al., 2023).",
    "According to Regulation EC Nr 1069/2009, insects used as food are regarded as Processed Animal Proteins (PAPs) in the EU (Smith & Barnes, 2015).",
    "Insects were no longer allowed to be used as animal feed as a result of Regulation EC Nr 999/2001's restriction on PAPs following the BSE crisis (EFSA Scientific Committee, 2015)."
